						<summary>

						<p>Rock near the steps leading to the temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">M.K. Rājakēsarivarman (Sundarachōḷa) Year 6: 963 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This registers a gift of 95 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp to the god of Tirumalai, a hamlet of Vaigavūr in Paṅgaḷa-nāḍu by Ēkavīraṉ Daṉmasaṅgātiyār <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Malaiyamahādēviyār, the wife of Malāḍu-uḍaiya Nāṭṭāṉ Sittavaḍattaḍigaḷ of <hi rend="italic">Bhārgava gōtra</hi> and the daughter of Nāḍāḷvār Iḷaṅgōṉaḍigaḷ.</p>						

